The paper deals with using visual grounding to improve speech systems, which falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The task of cross-lingual keyword spotting involves mapping keywords in one language to spoken utterances in another language, which could also fall under speech processing (cs.SD). The use of neural networks for this task also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
